<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-04-09T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-04-09T20:00:00-05:00" n="560" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d560">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.91262/236: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Leahy</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-04-09T20:00:00-05:00">April 9,
                                    1941—8 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>955. For Paris. Your 1073, April 7. The Department appreciates the
                            difficulties of the Allen case and has full confidence in your judgment
                            and that you will exhaust every possibility to obtain Allen’s
                            release.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>